        <p>At the phylum level, Firmicutes and Bacteroidetes were the most predominant phyla in the colon (<bold>Table <xref rid="T3" ref-type="table">3</xref></bold>). Infusion with SB tended to decrease the relative abundance of Bacteroidetes (<italic>P</italic> = 0.065) and to increase the proportion of Firmicutes (<italic>P</italic> = 0.093) and Spirochaetae (<italic>P</italic> = 0.093). Genus-level analysis of the top 30 most abundant genera revealed that unclassified Clostridiales, unclassified Ruminococcaceae, <italic>Clostridium sensu stricto</italic>, and <italic>Anaerotruncus</italic> in the colon were significantly increased in relative abundance by the SB infusion, whereas the abundance of <italic>Alloprevotella, Subdoligranulum</italic>, and <italic>Blautia</italic> was decreased (<italic>P</italic> &lt; 0.05) (<bold>Table <xref rid="T4" ref-type="table">4</xref></bold>).</p>
