      </sec>
      <sec>
        <title>Gene Expression of Inflammatory Cytokines</title>
        <p>In the ileum, SB infusion significantly down-regulated the gene expression of pro-inflammatory <italic>IL-6</italic> (<italic>P</italic> &lt; 0.05), and tended to decrease the gene expression of pro-inflammatory <italic>IL-12p40</italic> (<italic>P</italic> = 0.068), while had no effect on the gene expression of the other cytokines targeted in this study (<bold>Figures <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F5">5A,C</xref></bold>). In the colon, SB treatment decreased the gene expression of pro-inflammatory <italic>IL-6, IL-18, TNF-&#x3B1;</italic>, and <italic>IL-12p40</italic> (<italic>P</italic> &lt; 0.05), and tended to decrease the gene expression of pro-inflammatory <italic>IFN-&#x3B3;</italic> (<italic>P</italic> = 0.059), while increased the gene expression of anti-inflammatory <italic>IL-10</italic> (<italic>P</italic> &lt; 0.05). No difference in the gene expression of pro-inflammatory <italic>IL-8</italic> and <italic>IL-1&#x3B2;</italic> and anti-inflammatory <italic>TGF-&#x3B2;</italic> was observed between the two groups (<bold>Figures <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F5">5B,D</xref></bold>).</p>
        <fig id="F5" position="float">
          <label>FIGURE 5</label>
          <caption>
            <p>The relative gene expression of anti-inflammatory cytokines in the ileum <bold>(A)</bold> and colon <bold>(B)</bold>, and pro-inflammatory cytokines in the ileum <bold>(C)</bold> and colon <bold>(D)</bold> of pigs in the sodium butyrate (SB) and control (CO) groups. The values were calculated as the fold-expression change in SB group relative to CO group after normalization to the endogenous control, &#x3B2;-actin with formula 2<sup>-&#x394;&#x394;Ct</sup>. Values are expressed as mean &#xB1; SE, <italic>n</italic> = 6. <sup>&#x2217;</sup><italic>P</italic> &lt; 0.05, (<sup>&#x2217;</sup>)0.05 &#x2264;<italic>P</italic> &lt; 0.1.</p>
